Use the standard library
This is how to how_many_times of string and substring:
   Remember that n is string's length
   Remember that m is substring's length
   When m is 0, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   When n is less than m, then:
      The answer is 0
   End when
   Remember that count is 0
   Remember that limit is sum of (diff of n and m) and 1
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this limit times:
      Remember that match is 1
      Remember that j is 0
      Do this m times:
         Remember that ij is sum of i and j
         When item ij in string is not item j in substring, then:
            Remember that match is 0
         End when
         Increase j
      End do
      When match is 1, then:
         Increase count
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is count
